caption: I really, really wish they had a small option for $5 out the door.  Even the regular is a meal for 2 people, and it's not very good warmed up.

I am so disappointed. Only because my daughter has ordered from here a million times, and they do have pretty good food. But their customer service is lacking very much. They didn't have my phone number in their system because she always ordered under her phone number; therefore, they said because they were going to be closing in about 40 minutes and they didn't have my phone number in their system, they were not going to allow me to place my order. Not even if I paid for it, in advance, and then drive 5 minutes to pick it up. She said it was their policy. I have just never heard of such a policy.. not like that.. and honestly, I would totally understand if it was 10 minutes 'till closing. BUT it WASN'T! This is why I, nor my daughter, will  order from you again. You had plenty of time to cook food which takes 10 minutes to cook and I was willing to pay for it,in advance,  and even pick it ..when I originally wanted delivery. It just doesn't make any sense to me so that's that and it is what it is.. oh, and Benihana got our business.. and they even delivered and it was amazing food. Solo digo!!!

My company has been ordering from your establishment for many years.  We have been very loyal customers and spend a very large amount of money with you. Over the last several months we have had nothing but mistakes and issues with our orders.  The latest being that when we specifically asked that an order be made without onions and peppers our request was denied due to you being “too busy.”  But when we asked to add mushrooms on another order you were not “too busy” to do that. In our last order you charged us for a meal that we did not receive and when we called to let you know, you refused to do anything about the issue, and the time before that we had a similar problem that you refused to make right. Due to your lack of customer service and horrible people skills you have lost a very loyal customer.

I consider myself a hibachi connoisseur, and have been to over a dozen different ones all up and down the east coast. However, this little hidden gem is only my second "express" steakhouse, the first being Osakas in Lynchburg, Va.   Their is no doubt about the portion size, that everyone else is mentioning below, it is huge.  The regular size is perfect for an adult. Two children (10 and 8) can share a regular size too.  The chicken is what it is, chicken, nothing fancy. This particular restaurant clearly uses their own homemade sauce, as the chicken tasted just a little different then most places i've been to, note- that this is neither good nor bad, just different.   The yummy yummy sauce (Japanese steakhouse white sauce) had a small mayo after taste to it, which only means one of two things- either a.) they made it that day and didnt let it sit for 24 hours or b.) they didnt use Helmsmans (believe it or not, this makes a difference).   The price is great, the menu is standard hibachi, and there are about 6 tables available for eat in.  You can order the salad (with Ginger dressing) for $1.99.   I didnt see the soup that usually accompanies the meal, but I didnt really look for it either.  My only beef is - No chopsticks and homemade sweet tea (only the canned crap)----- two staples for Hibachi in my book!
